statement:
You are given a sequence $a_1, a_2, \dots, a_n$ consisting of $n$ non-zero integers (i.e. $a_i \ne 0$).
You have to calculate two following values:
•  the number of pairs of indices $(l, r)$ $(l \le r)$ such that $a_l \cdot a_{l + 1} \dots a_{r - 1} \cdot a_r$ is negative;
•  the number of pairs of indices $(l, r)$ $(l \le r)$ such that $a_l \cdot a_{l + 1} \dots a_{r - 1} \cdot a_r$ is positive;
